What is your social media content doing for you behind the scenes that you don’t even realize is happening…

There’s no such thing as coincidences on social media. You don’t just “randomly” get a dm from a stranger wanting to work with you.

None of these events are actually random but a system that is working wether you realize it or not.

What happens when you get a new lead? You call them up, get an idea of their timeline, and stay Infront of that person month after month until they’re ready to buy or sell. This could be 6 months to a year or even longer of follow up calls.

The difference with social media is that your posts are that follow up call but you’re reaching a large pool of people with every single post and all you have to do is be consistent…

And then boom when the time comes that the viewer is ready to buy/sell they’ve been consuming your content for months and you’re the first person they’re subconsciously thinking to reach out to.

They’ve seen the clients you’ve been helping, the value that you bring in your business, and a glimpse of who you are as a person.

You’ve stayed top of mind and they reach out to you when they’re ready which is why these transactions happen on a much quicker timeframe.

If you’re a real estate agent and want to know exactly what I mean by all of this 📲 dm me “MASTERCLASS” to attend my free upcoming social media training.

Exposure is everything when it comes to marketing your listing and the more exposure that you can offer your seller, the more value you bring to the table 🔥

The best strategy for marketing your listings on social looks like this: create multiple high quality short form videos to post on IG reels, FB reels, Tiktok, YouTube shorts, and even LinkedIn, create one long form video for YouTube and share the link across all platforms

It sounds like a lot of work but really should only take up a total of one efficient hour of your time. 20 minutes to film the content. 10 minutes to send it off to the editor. 30 minutes to write the copy and schedule the posts.

If you’re spending hours creating content or thousands paying someone else to, chances are you just don’t have your strategy dialed in

Different markets, same solutions🌵🏔️ I wish we had a crystal ball that could predict what interest rates will do.

Could they go up? Yes.
Could they go down? With time…

We do however know that there is always a cost when it comes to waiting. Right now buyers are still able to purchase a home and save money by asking sellers for a rate buydown. 💰

To paint a picture: if you ask for $10k off the sales price of $450k, you’ll reduce your mortgage payment by $75. 📉

✅ If you ask for $10k in seller concessions to buy down the rate, you’ll reduce your mortgage payment by $254 a month. ‼️

📲 If you’d like more information on this exact process dm “rates” to @maryanne_rosee for the Arizona market & @amandaaguiarofficial for the Seattle market
